        <div2>
          <head>
            <title type="main">
              <hi rend="b">Mrs. Blake Requests Her Portrait</hi>
            </title>
          </head>
		<q>
He keeps putting her off.<lb/>
She, in her quiet way, insists.<lb/>
Knowing he has a way with women,<lb/>
romancing them in paint<lb/>
the color of jewels, inventing<lb/>
their most flattering features,<lb/>
she expects he will exalt<lb/>
her wifely figure,<lb/>
the serviceable hips,<lb/>
hair ripe with oil and smoke.<lb/>
Over lunch he takes up<lb/>
a dull lead stub and sketches<lb/>
her profile: one miniature eye<lb/>
downcast, half a mouth<lb/>
and chin. Still chewing<lb/>
the last bite of fish pie,<lb/>
he adds a few squiggles for hair.<lb/>
Pushing it across the table,<lb/>
he trusts her to understand<lb/>
that when he rendered Beatrice<lb/>
crowned, Eve’s exquisite neck<lb/>
and Bathsheba disrobed,<lb/>
his vision was of Catherine.
</q>
          <byline>
            —<docAuthor><hi rend="i">Paulette</hi> <name><hi rend="i">Roeske</hi></name></docAuthor>
